### Problem

I started to notice this recently:

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/427282d6-0827-4ec1-848b-a7d2aa5f6cbb

In summary, when changing tabs on iterm2, using shortcuts or even by clicking on the tabs, that strange input gets inputed to neovim.

I tried reinstalling the latest stable version and it doesn't happen in there.

### Steps to reproduce

1. open nvim
2. go to insert mode
3. open another tab on iterm2
4. change tabs

### Expected behavior

Nothing to be inputed on neovim

### Nvim version (nvim -v)

v0.11.0-dev-1114+gad3472e291-Homebrew

### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?

no, vim 9.0

### Operating system/version

macOS 15.1

### Terminal name/version

iterm2 3.5.6

### $TERM environment variable

xterm-256color

### Installation

homebrew

- e41368f3bc1d08d900425608bd199f585d6fce59
- d8aee77a4e74b0ac886fee1b29f719314051f39c

@zeertzjq I'll see if I can bisect that soon, but the weirdest thing that I discovered:

The issue happens only when I have anything connected to my mac. e.g. if it is connected to the power cord, or connected to any USB-c device. If I unplug those then it will not happen anymore.

But only in neovim HEAD, it doesn't happen on latest nvim stable and neither on vim itself.

This sounds crazy, I know... never seen such behavior before, but commenting in case it rings any bell
